   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1836-12_page001.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Black-Castle_IE">Black Castle</placeName>
                  <date when="1836-12-03">Dec 3<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. 1836</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WilsL1">My Dear Lestock</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I must trouble you again - Read the enclosed letters<lb/>
               from <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BaldR1">Baldwin</persName> &amp; Co. &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BentR1">
                  <choice>
                     <orig>Bently</orig>
                     <reg>Bentley</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName> - See <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BaldR1">Baldwin</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#CradC1">Cradock</persName> &amp; settle<lb/>
               with them the first because I said they should have the first<lb/>
               offer a new <choice>
                  <orig>Ed.</orig>
                  <reg>Edition</reg>
               </choice> of <title ref="./Workography.xml#Helen1">Helen</title> - Also I think it just to repeat that offer<lb/>
               for their Collection in 18 <choice>
                  <orig>vols.</orig>
                  <reg>volumes</reg>
               </choice> of my work - But - I never did offer<lb/>
               to sell them the <hi rend="underline">remaining <choice>
                     <orig>Copy right</orig>
                     <reg>Copyright</reg>
                  </choice> of <title ref="./Workography.xml#Helen1">Helen</title>
               </hi>" If they mean<lb/>
               the whole <choice>
                  <orig>copy right</orig>
                  <reg>copyright</reg>
               </choice>, I will not - They must say what no<lb/>
               their <choice>
                  <orig>Ed<hi rend="superscript">n</hi>
                  </orig><reg>Edition</reg>
               </choice>. is to consist of &amp; which they do not in their letter state<lb/>
               the number &amp; price <hi rend="underline">proportionable I beg you</hi> to settle -<lb/>
               I would only observe that if they absolutely object to my<lb/>
               allowing <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BentR1">
                  <choice>
                     <orig>Benly,</orig>
                     <reg>Bentley</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName>
               <hi rend="underline">an</hi>
               <choice>
                  <orig>Ed<hi rend="superscript">n</hi>
                  </orig>
                  <reg>Edition</reg>
               </choice>. of any number for this standard<lb/>
               novels I should think it just that they should pay more than<lb/>
               if they agreed to permit me to deal with him for any certain<lb/>
               number for Standard novels - However small or large -<lb/>
               2<hi rend="superscript">ly</hi> for <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BentR1">Bently</persName> - If <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BaldR1">Baldwin</persName> objects to my letting him<lb/>
               have an Ed<hi rend="superscript">n</hi>. of <title ref="./Workography.xml#Helen1">Helen</title> &amp; if you arrange to accept of<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BaldR1">Baldwin's</persName> terms we have nothing to do but civilly to tell<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BentR1">
                  <choice>
                     <orig>Bently</orig>
                     <reg>Bentley</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName> so - And either you will do that &amp; or write to me<lb/>
               <hi rend="underline">But</hi> if <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BaldR1">Baldwin</persName> does<lb/>
               &amp; I will write to that effect to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BentR1">
                  <choice>
                     <orig>Bently</orig>
                     <reg>Bentley</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName>
               <hi rend="underline">But</hi> if <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BaldR1">Baldwin</persName> does<lb/>
               not come to terms with you then we have to deal with <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BentR1">
                  <choice>
                     <orig>Bently</orig>
                     <reg>Bentley</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName>
               <lb/>
               He says that he does mean to offer me 100 for the <hi rend="underline">whole</hi>
               <lb/>
               <hi rend="underline">copy right</hi> of <title ref="./Workography.xml#Helen1">Helen</title> - But only for a stereotype Ed.<hi rend="superscript">n</hi> might<lb/>
               be any number he might ever in future want for<lb/>
               Standard novels &amp; consequently this wd make the copy right<lb/>
               valueless to me or to any other publisher - this wd be in<lb/>
               fact <hi rend="underline">selling <del>the</del> my Copyright for 100 - </hi> which I will not do -<lb/>
               nor am I will willing to sell the whole copy right on any<lb/>
               <del>after</del> consideration (unless you my Dr Lestock advise it<lb/>
               &amp; even this I leave to <choice>
                  <orig>yr</orig>
                  <reg>your</reg>
               </choice> better judgment - I think that<lb/>
               whatever agreement is made should be in writing<lb/>
               &amp; begging you to settle with these Gentlemen publishers<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1836-12_page002.jpg"/>
               for me &amp; knowing you will make me deal <choice>
                  <orig>handsome<lb/>
               ly</orig>
                  <reg>handsomely</reg>
               </choice> &amp; consider credit for me more than money be<lb/>
               assured I shall be perfectly satisfied with what<lb/>
               ever you decide - only <hi rend="underline">decide</hi> for <choice>
                  <orig>yr</orig>
                  <reg>your</reg>
               </choice> obliged<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>
                  <del>I must decline <del>hav</del> giving <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BentR1">Bentley</persName>
                     <choice>
                        <orig>permis</orig><reg>permission</reg>
                     </choice>
                  </del>
                  <lb/>
                  <del>
                     <choice>
                        <orig>sion</orig>
                        <reg>permission</reg>
                     </choice> to insert <del>them</del>
                     <title ref="./Workography.xml#Helen1">Helen</title> at all in standard</del>
                  <lb/>
                  <del>no</del>
                  <lb/>
                  I beg you will see <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BaldR1">Baldwin</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#CradC1">Cradock</persName>
                  <lb/>
                  first as I proposed to give them the<lb/>
                  first offer - and settle with them<lb/>
                  as you think best -<lb/>
                  When that is done settle with <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BentR1">Bentley</persName>
                  <lb/>
                  And be assured that whatever you<lb/>
                  do for me I shall approve<lb/>
                  1836<lb/>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">M E</persName> to <unclear>Lhrtwn</unclear>
                  <lb/>
                  <choice>
                     <orig>ab<hi rend="underline">t</hi>
                     </orig>
                     <reg>about</reg>
                  </choice>
                  <title ref="./Workography.xml#Helen1">Helen</title>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
         </div>
